  {"instruction":"How does diagnostion feed results to soma_mind?","response":"After diagnostion_run(), results are passed to soma_mind_update_telemetry() as DiagTelemetry. soma_mind uses CPU feature flags to select inference path (AVX2/SSE2/scalar). Memory zone sizes set the warden pressure baseline.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":5},

  # diopion-engine
  {"instruction":"What is diopion-engine?","response":"diopion-engine routes bare-metal inference requests from the kernel REPL to the DIOP gateway on the host. It serializes GenerationRequest structs into UART packets and deserializes GenerationResponse from the response stream. No dynamic allocation.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":4},
  {"instruction":"What is the diopion UART frame format?","response":"DiopionFrame: { uint8_t sof[2]; /* 0xD1 0x0E */ uint16_t total_len; uint8_t worker_id; uint16_t goal_len; uint8_t goal[goal_len]; uint16_t crc16; }. Max 512 bytes. CRC16-CCITT over bytes 4..total_len-1.","domain":"code","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does diopion handle a gateway timeout?","response":"diopion_await_response() polls UART RX with deadline (10000ms via llmk_get_ticks()). On timeout returns DIOP_ERR_TIMEOUT. REPL prints '[diop] timeout' and falls back to local inference via gguf_infer or ssm_infer.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"Which workers does diopion support?","response":"diopion_worker_id() maps: analysis=0, baremetal=1, code=2, warden=3, compiler=4, qa=5, science=6, executor=7, architecture=8, refactor=9. REPL /diop <worker> <goal> calls diopion_send_request(ctx, worker_id, goal).","domain":"arch","dark_loops":4},
  {"instruction":"How does diopion receive a GenerationResponse?","response":"diopion_recv_response() reads response frame, validates CRC, populates DiopionResponse: { char summary[512]; char artifacts[4][256]; uint8_t risk_count; char risks[4][128]; }. REPL prints summary. Risks forwarded to warden.","domain":"code","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What role does diopion play in the evolvion loop?","response":"When evolvion records an unsatisfied need, it calls diopion_send_request(ctx, WORKER_BAREMETAL, need_description). diopion_recv_response() returns the C code artifact. evolvion validates and JIT-loads it if safe.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":6},

  # dreamion-engine
  {"instruction":"What is dreamion-engine and when does it run?","response":"dreamion-engine runs during OO's sleep phase (idle_ticks > DREAM_THRESHOLD). It consolidates inference logs, computes Hebbian weight micro-adjustments, and generates JSONL training samples for Batterfyl. Freestanding C11, no libc.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What does dreamion_pulse() do?","response":"dreamion_pulse(ctx): (1) reads last N journal entries, (2) scores by novelty+correctness, (3) calls llmk_hebbian_update() on high-score entries, (4) appends to dream_export.jsonl, (5) returns DreamSummary{result, ticks_taken, final_pressure, fail_reason}.","domain":"code","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does dreamion select which journal entries to process?","response":"novelty_score = hamming_distance(entry.token_hash, recent_hashes[]) / 64. correctness_score = entry.user_rating if present, else 0.5. Combined = 0.6*novelty + 0.4*correctness. Entries with combined > DREAM_THRESHOLD (0.7) are selected for Hebbian update.","domain":"system","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does dreamion export training data?","response":"High-scoring candidates are written to dream_export.jsonl: {\"instruction\": entry.prompt, \"response\": entry.response, \"domain\": \"system\", \"dark_loops\": round(score*7)}. DIOP Sleep Learning reads this on next wake cycle and merges into Batterfyl.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
