  # evolvion-engine
  {"instruction":"What is evolvion-engine?","response":"evolvion-engine records unsatisfied needs (hardware faults, policy violations, missing handlers) and uses diopion to request LLM-generated C code from DIOP's baremetal worker. Validated code is JIT-loaded into the HOT zone via function pointers.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does evolvion record an unsatisfied need?","response":"evolvion_record_need(ctx, kind, description): appends NeedRecord to ctx->needs[] (ring buffer, max 32). Kinds: NEED_MMIO_HANDLER, NEED_IRQ_HANDLER, NEED_POLICY_GAP. If full, oldest is overwritten. Each has retry_count to prevent infinite LLM loops.","domain":"code","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does evolvion validate LLM-generated code?","response":"evolvion_validate_artifact(code, len): (1) BareMetalValidator — no malloc/free/printf, volatile on MMIO. (2) GCC -fsyntax-only check via compiler worker. (3) Size < EVOLVION_MAX_CODE_BYTES (64KB). All three must pass before JIT-load.","domain":"policy","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does evolvion JIT-load validated code?","response":"evolvion_load_handler(ctx, code, len): (1) Copy to HOT zone executable page (4KB-aligned). (2) SetMemoryAttributes(EFI_MEMORY_XP clear). (3) Store function pointer in ctx->handlers[need_kind]. Future evolvion_dispatch(need_kind) calls through the pointer.","domain":"code","dark_loops":7},
  {"instruction":"What happens when evolvion exhausts retries?","response":"After EVOLVION_MAX_RETRIES (3) failed attempts, need is marked NEED_STATE_DEAD and warden_alert(WARDEN_EVOLVION_STUCK) is called. No further DIOP requests. Warden may escalate to quarantine mode.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does evolvion interact with D+ policy?","response":"Before JIT-loading, evolvion calls dplus_check(ctx->dplus, EVOLVION_JIT_OP, handler_base, handler_size). D+ verifies target is within HOT zone and size < 64KB. Rejection prevents load and logs a policy violation.","domain":"policy","dark_loops":6},

  # memorion-engine
  {"instruction":"What is memorion-engine?","response":"memorion-engine is OO's episodic memory engine. Stores token sequences and context summaries in COLD zone. Retrieves top-k similar contexts for prompt injection. Fixed-size memory arena, no dynamic allocation.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":4},
  {"instruction":"How does memorion store a memory entry?","response":"memorion_store(ctx, tokens, count, summary, len): (1) hash = CRC32(tokens[0..min(16,count)]). (2) Check duplicates in hash table. (3) Write to arena at write_ptr. (4) Advance write_ptr with LRU wrap. (5) Insert hash → offset into hash_table[].","domain":"code","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does memorion retrieve similar contexts?","response":"memorion_query_recent(ctx, N): returns N most recently written entries (walk arena backwards). memorion_query_similar(ctx, query, k): computes Jaccard similarity on first 16 tokens, returns top-k by score.","domain":"code","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What is the memorion heat score?","response":"heat_score (uint8_t, 0-255) per entry. On access: heat = min(255, heat + HEAT_INCREMENT). On dreamion_cool_all(): heat >>= 1 (halving decay). Entries with heat > 192 are candidates for WARM zone promotion.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does memorion integrate with the inference loop?","response":"Before each inference, llmk_oo_infer() calls memorion_query_similar(ctx, prompt_tokens, 3). Top-3 results are prepended to KV cache as synthetic context tokens, giving OO long-term episodic recall without retraining.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does memorion handle cold zone exhaustion?","response":"When write_ptr reaches arena_end - MEMORION_MIN_FREE, LRU eviction: scan entries, evict lowest heat_score. Clear slot, remove from hash_table[]. memorion_eviction_count tracks total evictions for warden monitoring.","domain":"system","dark_loops":4},

  # metabion-engine
  {"instruction":"What is metabion-engine?","response":"metabion-engine tracks OO's metabolic state: CPU cycles consumed, memory bandwidth, estimated thermal output from TSC delta. Signals starvation (budget exhausted) and fever (temp threshold exceeded). Influences D+ policy and dreamion scheduling.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":4},
  {"instruction":"How does metabion measure CPU cycle consumption?","response":"metabion_tick(ctx, phase): reads TSC at start/end, delta = end - start. ctx->phase_cycles[phase] += delta. Every METABION_WINDOW cycles: ctx->cycle_rate = total_cycles / elapsed_time. rate > budget triggers METABION_STARVATION.","domain":"code","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What is the metabion starvation state?","response":"METABION_STARVATION set when cycle_rate > budget_hz * 0.95. When starving: dreamion suspended, soma_mind pulse interval doubles, swarm sync frequency halves. WARDEN_STARVATION_ALERT emitted. Clears when rate < budget_hz * 0.80.","domain":"system","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does metabion estimate thermal output?","response":"estimated_temp_C = BASE_TEMP + (cycle_rate_GHz * THERMAL_COEFFICIENT). Calibrated at boot by 1M-cycle NOP loop + ACPI thermal zone read. Without ACPI: fixed coefficient of 8 deg C per GHz.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What is the MetabionReport structure?","response":"typedef struct { uint64_t total_cycles; float cycle_rate_ghz; float estimated_temp_c; uint8_t starvation; uint8_t fever; uint32_t phase_cycles[8]; /* prefill/decode/dream/swarm/warden/repl/idle/other */ } MetabionReport;","domain":"code","dark_loops":4},
  {"instruction":"How does metabion interact with soma_vitals?","response":"soma_vitals_tick() calls metabion_report(ctx, &report) and formats via my_snprintf. /vitals REPL command triggers this. Output: cycle_rate, estimated_temp, starvation flag, per-phase breakdown. fever flag adds a WARNING line.","domain":"arch","dark_loops":4},

  # morphion-engine
