  {"instruction":"How does morphion switch inference modes?","response":"morphion_set_mode(ctx, mode, params): (1) Drain current queue. (2) kv_persist_save(MORPH_SLOT). (3) Reconfigure ctx->pipeline function pointer. (4) kv_persist_load(MORPH_SLOT). Returns MORPH_OK. KV cache is always preserved.","domain":"code","dark_loops":6},
  {"instruction":"How does morphion handle MINIMAL mode?","response":"MORPH_MINIMAL skips alternate SSM layers (0,2,4... runs; 1,3,5... skipped). Activates when warden pressure > 0.75. Emits '[morph] MINIMAL mode active' via soma_uart_emit. Reverts to SERIAL when pressure < 0.60.","domain":"system","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"What triggers automatic morphion mode changes?","response":"(1) Warden pressure > 0.75 → MORPH_MINIMAL. (2) /reason --creative flag → MORPH_SPLITBRAIN. (3) Swarm consensus with multi_vote=true → MORPH_PARALLEL. All changes logged to oo-journal as MORPHION_AUTO_CHANGE.","domain":"policy","dark_loops":5},
  {"instruction":"How does morphion ensure KV cache consistency during mode switch?","response":"morphion_set_mode() calls kv_persist_save(KV_PERSIST_MORPH_SLOT) before any change. If new mode init fails (insufficient memory), calls kv_persist_load(KV_PERSIST_MORPH_SLOT) to restore. OO never loses conversation context during topology changes.","domain":"system","dark_loops":6},

  # synaption-engine
